Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language 
known for its simplicity and readability. It is designed 
to be easy to learn and write, making it an excellent 
choice for beginners and experienced developers alike. 

Python's syntax is clear and emphasizes code readability 
through the use of indentation and straightforward language 
constructs. 

This readability, often referred to as the "Zen of Python," 
is one of its defining features.